{{notability|1=Biographies|date=October 2017}}
{{eastern name order|Dobos Tas László}}{{Infobox writer | name = Tas László Dobos | image = DobosTasLaszlo.jpg | caption = Tas László Dobos in 1994 | birth_date = {{birth date|df=yes|1947|03|06}} | birth_place = [[Budapest]] | nationality = [[Hungarians|Hungarian]] | spouse = Ágnes Halász }} '''Tas László Dobos''' (born 6 March 1947) is a [[Hungarian poetry|Hungarian poet]] and [[philosopher]].
Dobos graduated from high school in 1965, and worked as a [[teacher]] between 1981 and 2013. Over more than three decades, he taught [[Hungarian literature|literature]], [[philosophy]], [[art history]], and [[history of religion]] to as many as 2,000 students.
